Package embedding.measures

Interface InterruptionMeasure<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of objects that may be compared by this measure
All Superinterfaces:
Measure<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AnyDiscreteFrechet, ApproxFrechet, DiscreteFrechet, IntegralDiscreteFrechet
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface
public interface InterruptionMeasure<T>
extends Measure<T>
An InterruptionMeasure imposes a distance function on some collection of objects. Measures can be used to define the dissimilarity of specific objects.

In the case of the InterruptionMeasure, only the interrupting distance calculation must be implemented. The exact distance calculation defaults to the capped distance calculation with infinity as the maximum.

See Measure for further information on measures in general.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Anton Ballmaier
